295
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,677
Yep.

296
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:02,476
Here we are.

297
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:05,717
- Look, I'm freezing.
- Yeah. My secretary's out today.

298
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:09,515
I apologise for the inconvenience.
You'll have to seat yourself.

299
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:17,993
So this is the office, huh?

300
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:25,149
Let's just sort this out without
that lawyer breathing down our necks.

301
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:27,476
- She's pretty intense, huh?
- No shit, man.

302
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:30,194
After she ambushed me,
I couldn't eat for two days.

303
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:34,552
My girlfriend forced some toast down
my throat this morning. I threw it up.

304
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:39,038
That's kind of a dry run for our next
three years in Penang Prison.

305
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:45,114
So you're gonna do this?
You're going back?

306
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:51,150
No.

307
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:54,953
You don't give a shit, do you?

308
00:29:57,160 --> 00:30:00,914
- You think I don't care about Lewis?
- That's what you're acting like.

309
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:03,076
You don't know
the first thing about me.

310
00:30:03,280 --> 00:30:06,909
Fine. All right. Then how come
you're so ready to slam the door on him?

311
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:09,873
I know something
about guys who have clubs and badges.

312
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:13,436
I've had my ass kicked by those
bastards. It's not how you think.

313
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:17,189
Doing something good
doesn't mean there'll be a happy ending.

314
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:20,437
- You could very easily die over there.
- Yeah.

315
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:24,155
- You think of that?
- This is the other side of the coin.

316
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:27,033
If this goes down, God forbid,
and Lewis hangs,

317
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:30,073
you don't think
this is gonna be headline news?

318
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:33,716
Sheriff, this is gonna follow you around
the rest of your life.

319
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:38,596
Whereas the other way we come home
heroes and the city throws us a parade?

320
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:41,792
Tony, you're a fucking boy scout.
You really are.

321
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,719
Listen to me, OK?

322
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:48,151
Lewis would have gone back
for either of us.

323
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:50,351
You know that.

324
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:56,278
That's why I'll never be mistaken
for Lewis McBride.

325
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:05,710
- Afternoon, Miss Eastern.
- Thank you.

326
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:12,233
<i>Beth Eastern? Hi. I'm MJ Major,
a reporter for the New York Examiner.</i>

327
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,590
- You're a what?
- A reporter.

328
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,958
Really? And what would you want with me?

329
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:21,993
Come on, Beth. I know
the hanging's in less than a week.

330
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:26,398
Press is exactly what you and the family
need for a public outcry.

331
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:28,909
- The family wants this kept quiet.
- Really?

332
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:33,636
In this instance, your interests and
the interests of the public converge.

333
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:37,276
- How did you find out about this?
- My sources at the State Department.

334
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:39,710
There's a blackout
at the State Department.

335
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:43,310
They passed the buck.
They sold it as diplomacy.

336
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:46,751
That's why you need me, and fast.
I can make this happen fast.

337
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:49,997
- In 48 hours, Lewis McBride can be...
- No.

338
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:54,990
Listen to me. Do you remember Singapore?
The American kid who graffitied a car?

339
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:58,192
Because of the media frenzy,
they had to cane the kid.

340
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:01,995
That was a caning.
To show some national backbone.

341
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,236
- This is a hanging.
- I know that.

342
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:08,479
Some Aussie dope dealer's mother went on
every talk show from Sydney to London.

343
00:32:08,680 --> 00:32:12,195
You know what happened? They hung
her son a week early to shut her up.

344
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,390
Excuse me, I've got a really big week.

345
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:19,319
Beth, I can make miracles happen
in a week.

346
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:23,957
Don't do this. Don't do it.

347
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:28,039
- Wait a minute. Why...
- What? Jesus Christ!

348
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:31,118
I'm sorry. I'm very sorry. Just...

349
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:39,948
Can I have that, please?

350
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,876
- Is he boyish?
- What?

351
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:46,275
Is he cute? Is he clean-cut?

352
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:50,029
- Cos if I put him on the front page...
- Give me some time.

353
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:55,718
Give me some time, some space,
and I'll give you your story.

354
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:03,277
When?

355
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:05,675
Soon.

356
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:11,235
I'm gonna call you, Beth.

357
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,198
What are you doing here?

358
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:34,275
- I have a tape I want you to watch.
- Yeah?

359
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,948
Jesus Christ, you don't let up, do you?

360
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:40,357
- I can't.
