371
00:34:23,640 --> 00:34:26,154
- Beer is all I really remember.
- That's it?

372
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:28,237
- Yeah.
- Wow.

373
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:31,910
- He didn't leave an impression then.
- Lewis? Are you kidding me?

374
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:36,636
- Have you spent a lot of time with him?
- I've never had a beer with him.

375
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:43,155
He is, honestly, Beth, one
of the sweetest people I've ever met.

376
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:46,511
Lewis is the kind of guy...
You'd have a beggar on the street,

377
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:51,032
and he'd just...
he'd touch them somehow, talk to them.

378
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:55,472
The guy could have an illness,
language barrier, whatever it was.

379
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:58,035
He just could see people, I guess.

380
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:02,671
Got a big heart.

381
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:06,555
Yeah. That's nice.

382
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:09,996
What else can you tell me about him?

383
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,760
You are good, aren't you?

384
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:16,111
Oh, Sheriff, what do you think about me?

385
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:19,039
I don't know.

386
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:22,312
You seem to think I have
all these wiles and stratagems.

387
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:25,951
I don't.

388
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:31,315
I have a man's life in my hands.

389
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,511
I get that.

390
00:35:35,560 --> 00:35:38,120
But let me ask you a question, Beth.

391
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:40,709
